abstract: Solid demand at a Treasury auction eased fears that the appetite for U.S. debt would dry up and force the government to pay higher interest rates.
snippet: Solid demand at a Treasury auction eased fears that the appetite for U.S. debt would dry up and force the government to pay higher interest rates.
lead_paragraph: The ups and downs of the credit markets steered Wall Street for another day on Thursday. But this time, the direction for stocks was up.

headline.main: This Time, Treasuries Push U.S. Markets Higher
headline.print_headline: Stocks Rise Despite Anxiety Over Credit
